- For vector/matrix types (VECTOR2, VECTOR3, etc.) it uses their built-in interpolation methods
- The most expensive cases are POOL_VECTOR2_ARRAY and POOL_VECTOR3_ARRAY which require:
  - Memory allocation for new arrays
  - Looping through all elements
  - Performing interpolation on each element

2. **Bottlenecks**:
- The string interpolation case has some inefficiencies:
